This function handles the initial setup phase for a UI element by translating structural declarations into functional widget states. It first applies basic, core properties and then iterates through declared members to set dynamic attributes.

```python
def init_widget(self):
        """ Initialize the state of the toolkit widget.

        This method is called during the top-down pass, just after the
        'create_widget()' method is called. This method should init the
        state of the widget. The child widgets will not yet be created.

        """
        widget = self.widget
        d = self.declaration

        #: Save ref id
        ref = d.ref
        CACHE[ref] = atomref(self)
        widget.set('ref', ref)

        if d.text:
            self.set_text(d.text)
        if d.tail:
            self.set_tail(d.tail)
        if d.style:
            self.set_style(d.style)
        if d.cls:
            self.set_cls(d.cls)
        if d.attrs:
            self.set_attrs(d.attrs)
        if d.id:
            widget.set('id', d.id)
        if d.draggable:
            self.set_draggable(d.draggable)

        # Set any attributes that may be defined
        for name, member in d.members().items():
            if not member.metadata:
                continue
            meta = member.metadata

            # Exclude any attr tags
            if not (meta.get('d_member') and meta.get('d_final')):
                continue

            # Skip any items with attr=false
            elif not meta.get('attr', True):
                continue

            elif isinstance(member, Event):
                continue
            value = getattr(d, name)
            if value:
                self.set_attribute(name, value)
```

Notice that attribute setting depends heavily on checking specific metadata, which ensures only intended data properties are applied while skipping events or excluded tags.

It skips applying any attributes where the metadata explicitly sets 'attr' to false. The check prevents unnecessary execution of the setter logic using this conditional block:
        elif not meta.get('attr', True):
            continue
